Is your app like this? Oh, that’s been done before
text:
You’re a social media company, like Instagram? That’s been done before

Phone, like the iPhone? That’s been done before

Car dealership, like Mercedes? That’s been done before

Bank, like JP Morgan? That’s been done before

Restaurant, like the Olive Garden? That’s been done before

Gym, like Equinox? That’s been done before

Tennis player, like Federer? That’s been done before

Human, like Adam and Eve? That’s been done before

Video platform, like Vibehut.io? That’s been done before

It’s allllll been done before, what you feel like working on is the only difference.

Ask HN: Why haven't we seen more designer babies yet?
text: I know He Jiankui (Chinese biophysicist who created the world's first gene-edited children in 2018) was recently released from prison but I feel like I haven't heard much in the space. I understand the moral conundrums of such research and the applications of it, but frankly I'm shocked that there haven't been people who still go through with developing designer babies given the allure of having more intelligent, healthy, etc. kids. Any ideas why this tech hasn't gotten more adoption? Or perhaps it is just that people will not disclose it now and there is actually a non-trivial amount of gene-editing of babies happening.
